<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1315,2064]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,1315,1341]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Uredinia</emphasis>
amphigenous, more abundant on the adaxial side, scattered, yellow orange, erumpent, subepidermal, associated with chlorotic yellow-orange spots, spots dark brown in severe infections. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1114,1295,1351,1377]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Urediniospores</emphasis>
ellipsoidal to broadly ellipsoidal or pyriform, rarely globose, (27–)30–39(–45) × (15–)19–25(–28) µm (n = 30), pale yellow to hyaline, spore wall 2–3 µm thick, echinulate, germ pores not visible. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[912,970,1423,1449]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Telia</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1315,2064]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">
A 28S rDNA sequence of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,590,1459,1485]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thaliae">
<emphasis box="[484,590,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">P. thaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[855,922,1459,1485]" name="Benin" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Benin</collectingCountry>
shares 100% (890/892) sequence identity with previously published sequences of 
<taxonomicName box="[528,633,1495,1521]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thaliae">
<emphasis box="[528,633,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">P. thaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<accessionNumber box="[697,815,1495,1521]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/JX206994" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">JX206994</accessionNumber>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Padamsee, M. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C." box="[826,1158,1495,1522]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref13056" refString="Padamsee, M. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. (2012) First report of Puccinia thaliae on canna lily in New Zealand and in some Pacific island countries. Australasian Plant Disease Notes 7: 139 - 141. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13314 - 012 - 0069 - 3" type="journal article" year="2012">Padamsee &amp; McKenzie 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
